  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Finance Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Overview</strong></p><p>We are seeking a hands-on Finance Manager to manage the full spectrum of finance and accounting functions for our healthcare business. This role plays a key part in ensuring financial accuracy, compliance, and supporting management with timely financial insights.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Manage full set of accounts including AP, AR, GL, bank reconciliations, and month-end/year-end closing.</li><li>Prepare monthly management reports, budgets, forecasts, and financial analysis.</li><li>Oversee clinic billing, revenue recognition, insurance and corporate receivables.</li><li>Manage cash flow, collections, and payments to suppliers and service providers.</li><li>Ensure compliance with SFRS, GST, IRAS, ACRA, CPF, and statutory requirements.</li><li>Liaise with external auditors, tax agents, banks, and other stakeholders.</li><li>Oversee payroll, including doctors’ remuneration and statutory submissions.</li><li>Drive process improvements and strengthen financial controls.</li><li>Support management on business decisions, cost control, and expansion initiatives.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Accounting, Finance, or equivalent; professional qualification (ACCA/CPA/CA) preferred.</li><li>Minimum 5 years of relevant experience with hands-on full set accounting.</li><li>Prior experience in healthcare or service-based industries is an advantage.</li><li>Strong knowledge of Singapore accounting standards, GST, and tax regulations.</li><li>Analytical, detail-oriented, and able to work independently.</li><li>Proficient in accounting systems and Microsoft Excel.</li></ul><p><strong>Why Join Us</strong></p><ul><li>Growing healthcare organisation with expansion plans</li><li>Opportunity to work closely with senior management</li><li>High-impact role with end-to-end finance ownership</li></ul>",
